You can use any of the clauses with any top-level operator, such as
[autocomplete](autocomplete-ref), [text](text-ref), or
[span](span-ref), to specify query criteria.

To optimize performance, place non-scoring operators such as
[equals](equals-ref), [range](range-ref), and [in](in-ref) in the
[filter](filter) clause to avoid unnecessary scoring operations. If you
want to run multiple operations that must be evaluated as an `OR`
condition, nest a [should](should) clause within the top-level
[filter](filter).

> **Example:**&#x20;
>
> ```javascript
> [
>   {
>     $search: {
>       index: "default",
>       compound: {
>         filter: [
>           {
>             compound: {
>               should: [
>                 {
>                   equals: {
>                     path: "accommodates",
>                     value: 2
>                   }
>                 },
>                 {
>                   range: {
>                     path: "pricePerNight",
>                     lte: 200
>                   }
>                 }
>               ]
>             }
>           }
>         ]
>       }
>     }
>   }
> ]
> ```

